Rakuten Shares Climb After JPMorgan Raises Recommendation to ‘Overweight’

-- B y   K a z u y o   S a w a
-- 
2011-05-19T01:25:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/rakuten-shares-rise-most-in-nine-weeks-after-jpmorgan-overweight-rating.html
     May 19 (Bloomberg) --  Rakuten Inc. (4755) ,  Japan ’s biggest online
retailer, climbed the most in nine weeks in Osaka trading after
JPMorgan Chase & Co. raised the stock’s investment rating.  Rakuten gained 4.9 percent to 79,300 yen as of 9:52 a.m. on
the Osaka Securities Exchange’s Jasdaq market, headed for the
biggest increase since March 16. The benchmark Topix index rose
0.3 percent.  Hiroshi Kamide, an analyst at JPMorgan, raised his rating
on Rakuten to “overweight” from “neutral” yesterday. Kamide
increased his share-price estimate for Rakuten to 90,000 yen
from 63,000 yen.  “Rakuten’s e-commerce business expects to grow,” Kamide
said by phone. “It’s a progress shift change from an
advertising-oriented business model.”  Rakuten reported net income of 6.91 billion yen ($85
million) for the first quarter ended March 31, up 1.4 percent
from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
